 The real ballistic drag-related offsets I confirmed are:

  - ballistics::ProjBallisticsProperties::mass = 0x04
  - ballistics::ProjBallisticsProperties::caliber = 0x08
  - ballistics::ProjBallisticsProperties::cx = 0x0C
  - ballistics::ProjBallisticsProperties::maxDistance = 0x10
  - ballistics::ProjBallisticsProperties::splinterMass = 0x1C
  - ballistics::ProjBallisticsProperties::velRange = 0x24
  
  This comes from FUN_01d84880, which is the member-registration function
  for ::ballistics::ProjBallisticsProperties.
  
  So if by dragOff the source/origin field for projectile drag
  coefficient, the offset is:

  - dragOff = 0x0C as cx

Also relevant runtime fields:

  - ballistics::ProjectileBallistics::kv = 0x10
  - ballistics::ProjectileBallistics::ag = 0x14
  - ballistics::ProjectileBallistics::state = 0x18
  - ballistics::ProjectileBallistics::prev = 0x34

  Those come from FUN_01d637c0.

  Short version:

  - Raw drag coefficient field: 0x0C (cx)
  - Derived runtime drag term: 0x10 (kv


  